# RateOple Project Architecture

## Executive Summary
RateOple is a web application built using a **Clean Architecture** approach on the backend (.NET 9) and a modern **Single Page Application (SPA)** framework on the frontend (Vite + React).

The project is currently in the initial scaffolding phase:
- **Backend**: Set up with Core, Infrastructure, and API layers. Identity (Auth) is configured in the DbContext.
- **Frontend**: Standard Vite + React template initialized.

---

## 1. High-Level System Design

The system follows a standard Client-Server architecture.

```mermaid
graph TD
    User[Clients] -->|HTTPS/JSON| Frontend[Frontend (Vite + React)]
    Frontend -->|API Calls| Backend[Backend API (.NET 9)]
    
    subgraph "Backend System (Clean Architecture)"
        Backend -->|Controllers/Endpoints| API[RateOple.API]
        API -->|References| Core[RateOple.Core]
        API -->|References| Infra[RateOple.Infrastructure]
        Infra -->|References| Core
        
        Infra -->|EF Core Identity| Db[(Database)]
    end
```

---

## 2. Frontend Architecture (React + Vite)

### Technology Stack
- **Framework**: React 19 (Hooks-based functional components)
- **Build Tool**: Vite (Fast HMR and bundling)
- **Routing**: React Router DOM v7
- **HTTP Client**: Axios
- **Linting**: ESLint + standard React hooks plugins

